  "del:hasArgument": [
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_cd5ce198-e613-4a44-b22e-fff2c283420a",
      "del:text": "hey everyone , what did you guys think about the solution"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_7f6ae835-0875-4766-9d27-dce39eb4f414",
      "del:text": "I was thinking it was just <CARD>"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_a6fbfcdf-5f3a-45d9-a567-66cb9c7d3da5",
      "del:text": "We only need to test the statement , \" If vowel , then evem \" not the other way around , so we only need to test the <CARD>"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_bb1da475-362f-4fb5-8a17-aef4281c076d",
      "del:text": "Yeah , I said <CARD> and <CARD> but now I agree with you"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_2da6e3a6-52fd-4d74-90c8-5090033a8e44",
      "del:text": "'I think it''s <CARD> and <CARD> because we have to know if even numbers and vowels go together and <CARD> should have a vowel on the other side'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_1e70b259-28bd-4643-ba73-a8ae65c75e3b",
      "del:text": "'I don''t think it is <CARD> since the statement doesn''t say that an even number has to have a vowel on the other side'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_714e2032-3407-49b0-9a06-a005f9f205a5",
      "del:text": "'We just need to test the rule , right ? So flipping <CARD> tests it by showing us if there''s an even number .'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_0e082770-f84a-47a5-b61b-f34acc45fcb8",
      "del:text": "<MENTION> is right ."
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_8b1dfa9c-6c46-423d-9597-f3f9455791f7",
      "del:text": "We dont need to know both though , it says if vowel , then even . It says nothing about the opposite , \" if even , thenvowel"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_5b8be40f-ddae-4455-b330-01227dda6492",
      "del:text": "the only other thing I thought was that maybe <CARD> is actually a good idea"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_d4475ec0-72bb-46fd-8e07-1a393fce6491",
      "del:text": "because if we flip <CARD> and its a vowel , it is disproven"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_47d4e4e7-8acb-4436-8679-48dc7a14eb50",
      "del:text": "'We can flip <CARD> to see if there''s a consonant , but I don''t think that tests the rule as well as flipping <CARD>'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_a0bf26f4-de02-4f9c-b7dc-d820a4dbbac0",
      "del:text": "mine says all cards with vowels on one side have an even number on the other"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_fb214cdb-9278-41ff-b124-67fc86c8aeaf",
      "del:text": "Right mine says that too ... but not all cards with an even number have vowels"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_2fa0abe1-1214-426f-add3-88a3e1c6c28b",
      "del:text": "i think we can eliminate flipping <CARD> and <CARD> due to that"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_64128491-1f4e-4794-b349-c5ea2cb8cbc5",
      "del:text": "right so we only care about the ones with vowels ... Think about it this way ... If we flipped the <CARD> and there was a B , say , does it disprove the rule ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_3c7443c2-33f1-427d-a1bf-8b82d505b647",
      "del:text": "'So do we think it''s just <CARD> ?'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_044c6016-56dc-4ac9-9f88-6ba66d353e74",
      "del:text": "Because we can test the rule with <CARD> but not necessarily with the others"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_103a91dc-ff9c-4597-8087-fd19babf62eb",
      "del:text": "i think we can test the rule with <CARD> if it happens to be a vowel"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_38443770-8292-427a-a955-2fc5d5b5c76d",
      "del:text": "There could be a rule that says \" Some cards with consonants have even numbers \" both those rules could be true"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_2c063af8-8426-4d7c-b2c1-8de3a8fede73",
      "del:text": "but it may be a wasted flip if it isnt"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_ce1ef870-7711-418a-b7bf-d9ce45987d11",
      "del:text": "I think <CARD> is there to throw us off"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_9e273a70-74c5-443a-b2d2-c4c5f7cfbca1",
      "del:text": "'That''s what I''m thinking ... we COULD use <CARD> to maybe see if the rule is true ... but <CARD> will definitely tell us if it''s true'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_76396395-4a59-4333-907e-9970eaf8a869",
      "del:text": "I agree , <MENTION>"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_0d372d97-5214-45bb-aa44-a79d236e6eac",
      "del:text": "'but we don''t know what all the letters on all the cards are'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_e9d875b2-9ffe-42e0-9dfe-f196b9000d60",
      "del:text": "Does it matter ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_1ba5bbac-5b55-41ec-9880-6e56e3884670",
      "del:text": "'we know <CARD> and <CARD> . we know that <CARD> it doesn''t matter since it is already even'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_f01d04e4-bf65-402f-96f1-3142dbff342f",
      "del:text": "'We''re just testing the rule , not proving it :)'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_9e7c26d3-0e03-4cfe-834e-3e31ef857b26",
      "del:text": "Thats the point <MENTION> , it doesnt matter ... All that matters is to test the assumption , which is all cards with vowels"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_36c5bf5d-4579-47d9-bd48-93ead1c85b4d",
      "del:text": "So do we agree that we will just check <CARD> and submit ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_507def90-2bda-4341-86c3-a10d33695087",
      "del:text": "yes"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_3ca9fa03-7496-49f1-a418-58c0eb704ceb",
      "del:text": "So then we just need <CARD>"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_4af3b070-013a-44ba-bc77-fd3efd132560",
      "del:text": "alright lets do it"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_fbdcfa25-5171-4046-8f4d-1aef62e9ee6a",
      "del:text": "'fair enough , i think that''s valid'"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_c73cb812-fbf7-4e2d-83c6-391ddaa83f27",
      "del:text": "<MENTION> , you good ?"
    },
    {
      "@type": "del:Argument",
      "del:identifier": "delidata_argument_70626f2a-000b-4184-a6c3-98e1ee37c0d7",
      "del:text": "yep all good"
